This bug is a **memory ordering race** (store-buffering litmus test) that only manifests on weakly-ordered architectures (ARM/POWER). On x86 TSO, after `smp_mb()` flushes the store buffer, the pre-GP write is globally visible, so the new task will always see it — the bad outcome is architecturally forbidden. Cannot reproduce on x86/QEMU.

